programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Cynthia Rothrock
programme.desc: Officially named, “Queen of the Martial Arts,” Cynthia Rothrock is considered one of the most historic figures in martial arts history. or five consecutive years, she was the undefeated World Champion in the karate tournament circuit. She has graced the cover of over 60 martial arts magazines and was inducted into the prestigious Martial Arts History Museum’s Hall of Fame at its inception in 1999. In the 1980s, she became one of the biggest box office draws in both Hong Kong and America for her action films. To date, she has starred in over 60 films and was also named “Queen of the Martial Arts in Films”. She continues to be one of the greatest advocates for the martial arts conducting countless seminars throughout the world.

programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Gerald Okamura
programme.desc: Officially called the "scariest man alive" by Black Belt magazine, we go behind the scenes of one of the most awesome Asian bad guys, Gerald Okamura. From his iconic role at the Hatchett Man in "Big Trouble in Little China," to his many appearances as an evil bad dude, we explore Gerald Okamura's history, his life and his legendary career as one of the top weapons experts in America. Gerald Okamura was inducted into the Martial Arts History Museum's Hall of Fame in 2003. Directed by William Ford with Director of Photography Jim Towns.

programme.title: Flash Legs
programme.desc: A band of thieves, known as the Eight Dragons, commit murder in the process of a stealing a treasure map. They decide three years is long enough for the heat to die down and allow them to search for their hidden fortune. But none of the thieves trusts any of his brothers-in-crime to keep the map that long. Their leader's solution is to cut the map into eight pieces, one for each bandit. Meanwhile, a pair of relentless lawmen is after them. One policeman is killed in their battle with the first bandit they find. The remaining cop, Fong Yee, is all the more determined to hunt down the other seven. One by one, he collects the pieces of the map as his flashy, flashing feet kick his opponents into submission or death.

This "super shocker of the century" was a smash hit upon its 1959 release. For architecture buffs, the home used for the exteriors of the haunted house was actually designed by Frank Lloyd Wright and built in 1924!

programme.title: The Little Princess (1939)

She plays Sara Crewe, the privileged daughter of Captain Reginald Crewe. When the Captain leaves to fight in Africa’s Boer War, Sara is enrolled into an upper-crust school for girls in London. All is well until Sara’s father is reported dead. When Sara’s intuition tells her the Captain is still alive, she begins hunting London military hospitals, culminating in what "Times’s" critic Janet Maslin called “...a happy ending sure to make even grown-up viewers cry.”

When things get out of hand, Lugosi kills his henchmen, who wind up as zombies in the cellar. Director Wallace Fox, who had already worked with Lugosi on two previous Monogram films, Spooks Run Wild and The Corpse Vanishes, comes through with a true horror gem.

Director William Nigh (Black Dragons, Desert Nights) helmed this Poverty Row thriller from a screenplay co­written by Hollywood legend Curt Siodmak (The Wolfman, I Walked With A Zombie). Who will you root for – the jungle beast, or the man of science?

With a cast that includes Dale Evans, George 'Gabby' Hayes, Lloyd Corrigan, and Tom Keene, director Frank McDonald gives us a fun thrill ride through old Santa Fe. Trigger is here, too!

programme.title: Flying Wild
programme.desc: The East Side Kids are at it again! The fifth installment of the beloved East Side Kids franchise from Monogram Pictures Corporation is another laugh-a-minute slapstick adventure that checks in with gang members Skinny, Danny Graham, Peewee, Algy Reynolds, and Scruno as they work at the Reynolds Aviation Company. Hilarity ensures when our gang suspects a doctor, who runs an air ambulance service, is secretly a spy transporting secret information from the plant to enemy agents.

programme.title: The Jungle Book (1942)
programme.desc: There couldn't have been a better way to showcase Rudyard Kipling's famous jungle tale than in eye-popping Technicolor under the fantastical direction of Zoltan Korda ("Sahara"), and filling the role of Mowgli with the legendary Sabu ("Elephant Boy," "The Thief of Bagdad"). This 1942 feature was nominated for four Academy Awards (including one for Miklós Rózsa's musical score) and serves as a nice companion piece to the beloved 1967 Disney cartoon. But beware; there are no singing animals here, just a darker, more realistic depiction of the jungle striking back at those who would violate its secret code!

The hotel has been the hiding spot of treasures by war criminals, and their only means to access it undetected is by murdering the hotel managers.

programme.title: The Milky Way (1936)

He plays Burleigh Sullivan, a timid milkman who finds himself in the seedy world of prizefighting. Though he thinks his success is based on his ability to duck, it’s actually because his manager is bribing his opponents to fall down! Adolphe Menjou and Lionel Stander also star in this little classic (dubbed “uproariously funny” by Time magazine). It’s from director Leo McCarey, a triple Oscar winner who gave us such great films as Duck Soup and Going My Way.

programme.title: Dishonored Lady (1947)
programme.desc: Unbridled passion…scandal…murder! This seductive crime drama slickly directed by Oscar nominee Robert Stevenson (“Mary Poppins”) stars classic beauty Hedy Lamarr as Madeleine Damien, the fashion editor of an upscale Manhattan magazine in the midst of a breakdown. Considered wildly controversial for its time, even after the Hays Office demanded large-scale omissions of what it considered to be gratuitous sex and violence, “Dishonored Lady” nonetheless represents yet another complex and daring performance from the matchless Lamarr.

programme.title: Mesa of Lost Women

Still, dig the crazy guitar and piano score which was purloined by Ed Wood Jr. for Jail Bait, and notice a couple of Wood regulars (Dolores Fuller and Lyle Talbot) in the credits. What you have here is a sort of cousin to the films of Ed Wood, but one that can stand on its own as being truly awful. Enjoy!

programme.title: Alice in Wonderland

programme.title: Boarding House Blues

programme.title: Combat Bulletins

programme.title: The Limping Man
programme.desc: A WWII veteran goes back to England after the war only to discover that his wartime sweetheart has got mixed up with a dangerous spy ring.

programme.title: The Three Stooges 75th Anniversary TV Special
programme.desc: Woody Harrelson hosts a special tribute to the Three Stooges in honor of their 75th Anniversary. In addition to classic Stooges routines, there are feature film clips, ultra-rare shorts, solo appearances, andTV performances, rare home movies, and interviews with Stooge family members and special guest stars. A must for any Stooge fan? Why soitenly!

programme.title: Girl Gang
programme.desc: A group of teen girls fall under the influence of a sinister gangster; they're soon hooked on drugs, working as prostitutes, and committing robberies. This Z-grade gem, filled with cheesy acting and awkward film effects, was produced by George Weiss, the schlockmeister who funded such "classics" as Glen or Glenda, and Olga's House of Shame. Timothy Farrell, who stars as "Big Boss Joe", appeared in many Ed Wood movies and other low budget features. He's at his sleazy best here!

programme.title: Swamp Fire
programme.desc: Johnny Weissmuller plays a man in Louisiana haunted by his experiences from the war.

programme.title: Angel and the Badman (1947)
programme.desc: Angel and the Badman stars John Wayne as wounded outlaw Quirt Evans. When sheltered by a Quaker family, he falls for the family's angelic daughter, Penelope (Gail Russel). Though she brings on a transformation in Quirt's hard-boiled character for the better, he is ever-obsessed with avenging the killing of his foster father. The first starring vehicle that John Wayne produced himself, Angel and the Badman is an unconventional Western romantic classic that is richly entertaining for both fans of Wayne and the Western genre.

programme.title: Fog Island
programme.desc: This strange mystery tale stars two of Hollywood's greatest villains - George Zucco and Lionel Atwill. Zucco (The Mad Ghoul, The Mummy's Ghost) is Leo Grainer, a former convict living on an island with his daughter. Seeking revenge on his old business partners, he lures them to his home where they are soon at his mercy. This forgotten nugget from Producers Releasing Corporation was directed by Terry O. Morse (Godzilla, King of the Monsters) and is an excellent example of the "old dark house" mysteries from Hollywood's Poverty Row.

programme.title: “The Inside Story”
programme.desc: Short Industrial Training film produced by Jam Handy.

programme.title: Ghost Towns of the High Sierras
programme.desc: Hosted by Rip Torn, this documentary footage explores the Ghost Towns of the Old West.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 9
programme.desc: Guest starring Richard Chamberlin, and Gloria Loring amidst a series of comedic skits.

programme.title: Season 27 Episode 14
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Blacksmith
programme.desc: Buster clowns around in a blacksmith's shop until he and the smithy get in a fight which sends the smithy to jail. Buster helps several customers with horses, then destroys a Rolls Royce while fixing the car parked next to it.

programme.title: Condemned to Live
programme.desc: When a peaceful European village is suddenly plagued by a string of gruesome murders, the nocturnal attacks are pegged on a mysterious giant bat. But the real culprit is mild-mannered, respectable Paul Kristan, a kindly professor with an enigmatic ailment that transforms him nightly into a bloodthirsty vampire. Directed by horror aficionado Frank R. Strayer and produced independently, this film bears many of the hallmarks of a Universal prestige picture, and was a rarity for its time, considering its relatively sympathetic treatment of vampires.

programme.title: All the Kind Strangers
programme.desc: Beware of what’s hidden in the woods! In this thriller from Burt Kennedy, a band of orphans is more than they seem to be. Behind those kind faces lies murderous intentions if you don’t play along with their games. John Savage, Samantha Eggar, and Stacy Keach star in this thriller from the golden age of TV movies!

programme.title: Attack of the Giant Leeches (1959)
programme.desc: Massive bloodsucking monsters are at large in this Drive-in schlock classic from producers Roger and Gene Corman. The legendary Yvette Vickers (Attack of the 50-foot Woman) stars along with Jan Shepard, Ken Clark, and some nasty giant leeches! Basically, they're just a bunch of actors in plastic costumes, but director Bernard Kowalski (Hot Car Girl, Night of the Blood Beast) made the most of his small budget. When the Cormans wouldn't hire a crew to push the camera raft while filming water scenes in the Pasadena Arboretum, Kowalski put on a bathing suit and did it himself!

programme.title: Graverobbers
programme.desc: A waitress weds a mysterious funeral director.

programme.title: Food (1958)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Show

programme.title: Intimate Interviews - Bela Lugosi
programme.desc: 1931 interview with Bela Lugosi.

programme.title: The Ape Man
programme.desc: This campy yet compelling horror classic stars none other than the legendary Bela Lugosi as Dr. James Brewster who embarks on an ill-fated endeavor to find an antidote after he turns himself into a hairy, stooped-over ape-man. When Dr. Brewster discovers that the key ingredient of the antidote is recently drawn human spinal fluid, he is abandoned by his assistant and must rely on the help of his captive gorilla to aid him in his search for an appropriate donor.

programme.title: The Boys from Brooklyn (1952)
programme.desc: Duke Mitchell and Sammy Petrillo, a pair who made a brief career out of being dead ringers for Dean Martin and Jerry Lewis, play a couple of Brooklyn chumps stranded on the Pacific island of Cola-Cola where a mad scientist (Bela Lugosi) is conducting some hair-raising experiments. This oddity was also released as Bela Lugosi Meets A Brooklyn Gorilla, but no matter what you call it, this is a horror film that will stiffen you with laughter! Also, look for the great Ray ‘Crash’ Corrigan in the gorilla suit…

programme.title: Bowery at Midnight
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi is a college professor by day and runs a soup kitchen and hospital by night in New York City's Bowery section - but it's just a front for more sinister activities. When things get out of hand, Lugosi kills his henchmen, who wind up as zombies in the cellar. Director Wallace Fox, who had already worked with Lugosi on two previous Monogram films, Spooks Run Wild and The Corpse Vanishes, comes through with a true horror gem.

programme.title: White Zombie (1932)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: The Corpse Vanishes
programme.desc: Horror to make your hair stand on end! Another Monogram Pictures horror classic starring the inimitable Bela Lugosi, The Corpse Vanishes is an eerie, unsettling mystery about a mad scientist (Lugosi) who injects his aging wife with fluids from virginal young brides in order to preserve her beauty. Noted as one of the most successful and imitated collaborations between Monogram and Lugosi, this film’s plot bears an uncanny resemblance to the real world story of the murderous Elizabeth Bathory.

programme.title: Scared To Death
programme.desc: The only color film to star Bela Lugosi was this mystery thriller from director Christy Cabanne (The Mummy’s Hand) made for the short­lived Golden Gate Pictures during the early months of 1946. Lugosi plays Professor Leonide, a cagy character who may have had something to do with the death of a young woman (who happens to be telling her tale from a slab at the morgue!). George Zucco, Molly Lamont, and Joyce Compton also star, as well as Angelo Rossitto, (Freaks) as a menacing dwarf with a habit of stepping on Lugosi’s foot!

Andrew, who has Cerebral Palsy and uses a wheelchair, remembers the excitement of going to a gay bar for the first time and the reality that sets in once he arrives. Jason was a ballet dancer during most of his teenage years and into his 20s. He was celebrated for being thin. During one of his first times at a gay bar, he was told he's too skinny and needed to put on some muscle, leading him down a path of taking testosterone and being unhappy. It wasn't until he realized he needed to be happy with who he was because "I wasn’t happy pretending to be someone else." Growing up in a religious household, Benjamine was concerned about having to come out to his mom not only as gay, but as the owner of the successful porn company CockyBoys and being in a polyamorous relationship with two other guys. What he learned from the experience was that “honestly is the best thing in life.” At 5 years old, Noah Michelson did a seductive dance in his underwear for the family's garbage man. After being called "queer", Noah finally had a word to define who he was and how he felt. Renee has always been a tomboy, and now identifies as queer. When Renee was a teen, a neighborhood mom noticed how Renee dressed and took them (Renee uses "they/them/their" pronouns) to The Gap to buy them feminine-looking pants. The experience was traumatic, but also transformational. An inappropriate encounter at her job, related to her gender expression, led her to find a new job. Tori Baker went from a rough childhood to drugs to having a daughter and turning her life around. The turning point was realizing that she "can be who I am and like the people that I like.” Mitch was afraid that the relationship might end, but knew it was time to tell his girlfriend that he's transgender. programme.title: Her Story
programme.desc: S1 E1-3 | Violet, a waitress in Los Angeles, is approached by a reporter named Allie for a story about transgender women. Paige, an attorney for Lambda Legal, works on a case representing a trans woman who was denied entry into a women's shelter./Allie and Violet's interview lunch takes a flirtatious turn, and Allie learns that her friend Lisa holds some views that surprise her. A handsome stranger catches Paige's eye./Paige goes out to dinner with James, and it goes a bit differently than her typical dates, while Allie and Violet find they have more in common than they realized.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Between The Miles
programme.desc: Florence, a struggling musician, takes three homeless teens off the streets of Los Angeles and into her care only to realize she has to overcome her own reckless tendencies in order to care for them.

programme.title: No Gender! The Queer Life Of An Intersex Manga Artist
programme.desc: Up until age 30, Sho Arai lived as a woman, but was found to be intersex after chromosome testing.

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E1 | The four most powerful African American women in politics share the story of their friendship and how it has changed politics in America. Join the authors in a discussion about the book and how their careers evolved, while offering advice to Black women who dream of working in the field.

programme.title: Drag Kids
programme.desc: Drag has always been about breaking down barriers and daring to do the unexpected. Now, a new type of queen is on the scene: she’s fierce, she’s living in a time of unprecedented access to queer culture, and she’s younger than ever before. She’s a drag kid and she’s a long way from the era of the queens who led the Stonewall Riots nearly 50 years ago. Stephan, Jason, Bracken and Nemis have never met, but they’re united by a shared passion for drag. They are about to come together for the first time – to perform Lady Gaga’s ‘Born This Way’ at the world-famous Montreal Pride Festival. As they prepare for the big show, each faces their own unique challenges, as well as challenges they have in common - deep feelings of isolation and the struggle of trying to claim a place of your own on the fringes of a fringe culture. Drag Kids is a beautiful, daring, and touching portrait of four kids chasing freedom and friendship through the art of drag.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Between The Shades
programme.desc: A look into what labels a life in current LGBT America. Fifty conversations exploring the many different shades of being “gay” in America. This conversation focuses on the degrees and varying perceptions about how people define themselves, their lives, struggles and triumphs.

programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.desc: From an undisclosed location, Agent Roy drops more exclusive video from Professor Avi Loeb and Arik Kershenbaum about life, and living in the Universe

programme.title: Space Channel Special Report- NS 18 wrap up
programme.desc: Watch the best moments of the historic second human spaceflight mission from Blue Origin as well as the launch of the LUCY mission to the Trojans.

programme.title: Elon can't help but help
programme.desc: From water crises, ventilators and cave diving, Elon Musk, founder of Tesla and SpaceX just can't help but help.

programme.title: Mars Update
programme.desc: History is in the making as the United States, China and United Arab Emirates all set their sites on Mars. New technology and new hope for the future will all be on display. Space Channel gives an overview of each mission and the latest updates.

programme.title: Space Channel Exclusive- I4's Dr. Sian Proctor
programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: SpacedOUT! with Sarah Begum
programme.desc: After exploring remote corners of Planet Earth, living with indigenous tribes, surviving dangerous slums and working with societal skyscrapers, Sarah has taken her adventurous missions to a whole new level as she looks to the sky and space for her next phase of exploration. Maybe she is the one to make contact with alien civilizations? Or unearth and pioneer new discoveries and developments within the space industry. Find out...

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Yellowstone (1872)
programme.desc: Most of Earth’s geysers are preserved in Yellowstone, including Old Faithful, and they represent the main reason the land became America’s first national park in 1872. Home to mountains and abundant wildlife, Yellowstone is the core of one of the last natural ecosystems in Earth's temperate zone.

programme.title: Yosemite (1890)
programme.desc: First protected in 1864, Yosemite National Park is best known for its waterfalls, but within its nearly 1,200 square miles, you can find deep valleys, grand meadows, ancient giant sequoias, a vast wilderness area, and much more.

programme.title: British Columbia: Vancouver and Beyond
programme.desc: The vibrant city of Vancouver blends the call of the wild with big city charm. Tour historic Gastown and the Capilano Suspension Bridge. Vancouver Island’s capital city, Victoria, defines itself by all things British. Experience ziptrek flights through treetops, and cruise Alaska’s Inside Passage.

programme.title: Canadian Rockies Banff and Jasper
programme.desc: Explore a region famed for its hot springs, backcountry treks, and fantastic array of wildlife, and be treated to elegant dining, and chateaux retreats. Also, enjoy train rides aboard the Rocky Mountaineer, scenic drives along the Continental Divide, and Snocoach rides across treacherous ice fields.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Christmas in Americas National Parks
programme.desc: It is Christmastime in America’s national parks. Yosemite, Yellowstone, Grand Teton, and Grand Canyon National Parks each offers Christmas visitors their own unique versions of comfort, joy, and the warmth of vintage lodges during the holiday season in the form of festive activities and gatherings.

programme.title: Inside Grand Canyon National Park
programme.desc: Experience the supreme and sacred spectacle of the Grand Canyon. This insider’s view of one of the world’s greatest natural wonders takes you rim-to-rim to hike hidden canyons, plunge into ancient pools, raft world-class rapids, discover manmade gems, and explore extreme backcountry.

programme.title: Darwin Northern Territory
programme.desc: In Darwin, Jason swims in the Crocodile Tank and visits Litchfield National Park. He also goes heli-pubbing, savours the delicious barra burger, then catches, and cooks, black pepper mud crab. Delicious!

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Yazd, The Zoroastrian Fire Temple
programme.desc: Marvel at the pleasure gardens of Fin in the oasis of Kashan. In the nearby mountains, visit the temple of Chak Chak and become introduced to the ancestral religion of Zoroastrianism. In the sacred city of Yazd, visit a zurkhaneh, or a "house of strength," where athletes engage in training sessions.

programme.title: Bukhara, Light of Transoxiana
programme.desc: Halfway along the ancient Silk Road we arrive in Uzbekistan, first visiting the glorious city of Bukhara, the hometown of Avicenna, and renowned artists and craftsmen. The city’s bazaar is the beating heart of the city, and a bubbling melting-pot of cultures where all manor of items are sold.

programme.title: Samarkand, Pearl Among Cities
programme.desc: Some used to say Samarkand in central Uzbekistan was the center of the world. Follow the ancient "Royal Road" to the city associated with the great Turco-Mongol warrior Timur, visit his mausoleum, and learn about the imposing public square of Registan with the help of a local historian.

programme.title: Fergana, A Central Asian Melting-Pot
programme.desc: The modernity of life in Uzbekistan’s capital of Tashkent is readily apparent, as is the incredible mix of ethnic groups that exist here. Visit a silk factory, a must for anyone retracing the Silk Road, then travel the age-old route through the mountains to Kyrgyzstan, the land of the nomads.

programme.title: How to Be a Carioca
programme.desc: What is a Carioca? The natives of Rio de Janiero, Brazil are lovable scamps who find ways to avoid work, preferring the beach, flirting, and hanging out at restaurants and bars instead. Tony, under the tutelage of an exemplary Carioca, gives the lifestyle a try.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: Delhi and Agra, India
programme.desc: From the serene beauty of one man's architectural love poem to a woman, the Taj Mahal, to the crowded alleys of downtown New Delhi, India is a feast for the senses. Maxa discovers temples straight out of Disneyland and consults a street astrologer who tells him he will live a long life.

programme.title: Rajasthan, India
programme.desc: Tour the royal rooms behind the sandstone walls of the Mehrangarh Fort, perched high above the city of Jodhpur. In the countryside outside of Jodhpur, villagers, who have never seen a Westerner, invite Rudy Maxa into their homes, and the maharajah of Jodhpur explains why his palace is now a hotel.

programme.title: Istanbul, Turkey
programme.desc: In Istanbul, evidence of historical invasion exists everywhere. From the Romans to the Ottomans, this tumultuous city has seen it all, and its architecture, cuisine, and customs reflect that reality. Tour the Grand Bazaar, Topkapi Palace, the Hagia Sophia, the Blue Mosque, and the Spice Market.

programme.title: Turkey's Turquoise Coast
programme.desc: Ancient towns of Ephesus, Antalya, Myra and Dalyan dot the Turkish coast, tempting visitors to step back in time when lavish Roman homes and markets dotted the landscape. Boarding a gulet, the traditional wooden Turkish boat, for a Blue Cruise, Rudy departs from the popular seaside town of Bodrum.

programme.title: Bangkok, Thailand
programme.desc: Rudy takes you off the beaten path into the quiet, residential klongs, or canals, of Bangkok. Marvel at the Emerald Buddha, visit the city's fresh markets, join locals offering incense and flowers at colorful outdoor shrines, celebrate the king's 80th birthday with an all-night party, and more.

programme.title: Thailand, The Golden Triangle
programme.desc: The saffron robes of Buddhist monks, the vivid colors of local blossoms, and the brilliant emerald of rice fields make the Golden Triangle a magical corner of the world. Join Rudy as he takes mahout lessons and gets soaked steering his elephant into the river that separates Thailand from Burma.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: France's Via Aquitania
programme.desc: Follow the Via Aquitania, an ancient Roman road that connected a network of cities and was the main trade route between the Mediterranean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean. Traces of the region’s history abound and will become clearer to you the more you hear the people who love this land speak of it.

programme.title: The Volga, Soul of Russia
programme.desc: The Volga River, also called "matuschka,” welcomes world travelers on giant boats. Take a journey of 4,000 kilometers towards the Caspian Sea, from Moscow to Astrakhan, through Laroslav, Nijini Novgorod, Kazan, Samara, and Saratov.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: How to Be a Carioca
programme.desc: What is a Carioca? The natives of Rio de Janiero, Brazil are lovable scamps who find ways to avoid work, preferring the beach, flirting, and hanging out at restaurants and bars instead. Tony, under the tutelage of an exemplary Carioca, gives the lifestyle a try.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Brazil - A Preserved Beauty
programme.desc: Fernando de Noronha is an archipelago of 21 islands and islets in the Atlantic Ocean. The wild, natural beauty found above and below the sea are the main attractions of the region, where you can observe sea tortoises, dolphins, albatrosses, and some of the most stunning beaches on Earth.

programme.title: Egypt - Water And Sand
programme.desc: Siwa is an island-oasis of fire-torched skies in the middle of the Egyptian desert where The Great Sand Sea comes to rest at the foot of an oasis of date palms. Bordered by two lakes of turquoise blue, travelers find themselves at an oasis that is authentically North African.

programme.title: From Chicago to the Karoo
programme.desc: A healthy mind, body, and environment are all critical for living happy and productive lives. Meet pioneering people in Iraq, Colombia, South Africa, Indonesia, the United States, and Italy who believe in living symbiotically with nature.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Montreal, Canada
programme.desc: Join Donna in Montreal and experience the cultural and Epicurean wonders found in this amazing city in Quebec. Also, go jet boating and learn why Montreal is the unofficial "world headquarters" for the circus arts.

programme.title: S8E12 - Berlin
programme.desc: While visiting Berlin's powerful sights — moving memorials, top-tier museums, surviving bits of communist and fascist days — we'll take time to revel in its vibrant social scene.

programme.title: Sydney New South Wales
programme.desc: In Sydney, Jason takes part in some cooking at the award-winning Marque restaurant and meets with an up-and-coming pastry chef at The Blackstar Pastry. For some fun activities, he tries grape stomping and quad biking.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: A Taste of Tokyo
programme.desc: Anthony travels to Tokyo, where he begins in the Tsujiki market and then is introduced to techniques in preparing edomae sushi. He also learns the diets of Sumo wrestlers.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Kyrgyzstan, The Freedom of the Steppes
programme.desc: Osh is first on the list in Kyrgyzstan. Saunter down the aisles of the city’s bazaar and it will soon become clear to you that true Kyrgyzstan is to be found on the steppes and in the mountains. Discover Kyrgyz identity from a student who imparts local legends at the foot of the "Throne of Solomon.”

programme.title: Kashgar, The Gateway to the Middle Kingdom
programme.desc: Kashgar is our point of entry into China. Covering one-sixth of China’s surface area, Kashgar is home to the Uyghurs, an ethnic minority descended from Turkic peoples. When trade on the Silk Road was as its height, Kashgar was a major hub for caravans traveling to India or Central Asia.

programme.title: Taklamakan, The Forbidden Oasis
programme.desc: In ancient times, caravanners considered themselves safely in China only after they had first successfully negotiated the treacherous Taklamakan desert. In the dunes of Dunhuang, you will meet a camel breeder, and stretching outward from Dunhuang, witness The Valley of the 1000 Buddhas.

programme.title: Gobi, The Forbidden Oasis
programme.desc: An Uyghur family invites you into their home where you will learn about their way of life. Gaochang was once an important waystation on the Silk Road and famous center of learning. You will also visit the city of Turpan, in the heart of the desert, and tour its ingenious water-supply system.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: South Africa
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa knows that an adventurous safari is a wonderful way to experience South Africa. Get up-close-and-personal with lions, giraffes, elephants, and dozens of other animals in their natural habitat, thanks to robust preservation laws in place.

programme.title: Edinburgh and the Scottish Highlands
programme.desc: Climb the ramparts of Edinburgh Castle. Tee up at the world's most famous golf course, St. Andrews. Tour Deward's whiskey distillery. Stroll Stirling's historic battlefields of Braveheart fame. And, sail the bonny banks of legendary Loch Lomond.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: Rudy answers London's call with an expert tour of its traditional sights and contemporary, cutting-edge attractions. In London's breathtaking countryside you will find mythic castles, the real Alice in Wonderland's candy store, Jane Austen's house, and the mysterious megaliths of Stonehenge.

programme.title: Uzbekistan
programme.desc: In one of his series' most colorful episodes, Maxa takes viewers along the Silk Road in a country that is an emerging economy in Central Asia, Uzbekistan. Marvel at eye-popping mosques built centuries ago, and Rudy joins a family for the preparation of the national dish of "plov."

programme.title: Cape Town
programme.desc: Cape Town is a nexus of cultures in a setting so stunning it is called “Africa's Riviera." Where else in the world can you wake up in a cosmopolitan city, spend the afternoon with penguins, ride a funicular to the edge of the continent, and watch the sun set from a beach with a glass of wine?

programme.title: Garden Route
programme.desc: The Garden Route takes you along a rugged, gorgeous South African coastline. Surfers brave enormous waves and exotic birds watch visitors climb serpentine paths that rise above the coast amid seaside resort towns. Also, visit South Africa's lush wine country in the village of Franschhoek.

programme.title: Korea
programme.desc: From the bustling city of Seoul with its 10 million residents to the country's quite countryside, South Korea is a traveler’s paradise. With their misty mountain temples and the uber-modern cities, Koreans mix an abiding sense if history and traditions with a zeal to achieve global success.

programme.title: Best of the National Parks
programme.desc: Each year millions from around the world visit America's national parks, lured by images of lands of wonder beyond expression. This exhilarating program reveals the very best locations in America’s national parks to gaze at geysers, spot wildlife, mountain climb, spelunk, and even tie the knot.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Livingstone
programme.desc: “The Road of Livingstone” is a long journey in the footsteps of the British explorer David Livingstone along the Zambezi River, from its mouth in Mozambique all the way to Victoria Falls, at the border of Zambia and Zimbabwe.

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: Belize
programme.desc: Un-Belizable! We are off on a Central American Mayan excursion. We head up the steps of the ancient high temple at Lamanai. Then we take a city tour of the main tourist destination, Belize City. We learn about Belize's colonial roots at the Belize City History Museum and dive the amazing Blue Hole.

programme.title: Ottawa
programme.desc: We visit Canada's capital city-on-a-hill in Ottawa, Ontario. Sail down the famous Rideau Canal locks, go deep into Ottawa's Cold War history at the Diefenbunker, and explore Canada's military history at the Canadian War Museum. Then, head up the Peace Tower and visit the Library of Parliament.

programme.title: Mexico - A Desert Between Two Seas
programme.desc: The Baja Peninsula juts out into the Pacific Ocean like an icicle. The dazzling arid peninsula is a succession of sunset-kissed beaches and trickling creeks. Each year, millions of whales come to reproduce in the preserved waters of the peninsula that their whale ancestors knew so well.

programme.title: South Africa - A Rainbow Nation
programme.desc: With its wide-open spaces and pristine coastline, the province of KwaZulu-Natal has become one of South Africa's ecotourism havens. Away from the carefree atmosphere of its beaches, become a privileged witness to KwaZulu-Natal's well-preserved flora, fauna, and wildlife, possibly “The Big Five?”

programme.title: From Ithaca to the Amazon
programme.desc: Our natural environments are intrinsically more valuable than any grand visions of wealth created using methods detrimental to the Earth. Meet people in New York, India, Russia, Peru, Sumatra, and South Africa who favor health over profit.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: France's Burgundy and Loire Regions
programme.desc: The Burgundy region boasts top French wines, romantic canals, Romanesque churches, and world-renowned French cuisine. We base in the small town of Beaune and learn about its history of exceptional winemaking. Add a wondrous hot-air balloon ride over the verdant Loire Valley to the itinerary.

programme.title: Berlin
programme.desc: With world-class cultural sites, dynamic new architecture and unstoppable energy, Berlin is a city on the move. We visit the museums - the ancient treasures of the Pergamon and the Egyptian museum, German Expressionism at the Neue Nationalgalerie and the newly designed Jewish Museum.

programme.title: Catalina Island
programme.desc: Catalina Island, California is a unique island off the coast of California, and Donna will take you on a journey there to revel in the island’s history, art, cuisine, and have some fun horseback riding.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Aarhus
programme.desc: Welcome to Aarhus, Denmark, a city that illuminates the essential societal values Dans hold dear, values that include trust and honesty, health and happiness, and a strong belief in your fellow people. Alexandra comes to find out that collaboration can lead to prosperity.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: Lanzhou, On the Yellow River
programme.desc: Travel to Liqian, located at the narrowest point of the Hexi Corridor. Legend states that Liqian is where descendants of Crassus' lost legions ended up. Next, visit the sprawling industrial metropolis of Lanzhou on the Yellow River, and sample an essential ingredient of Chinese culture - noodles.

programme.title: Xi'an, The Capital of the Sons of Heaven
programme.desc: After arriving in Xi’an, you find yourself in the very spot where the caravans of the ancient Silk Road ended their arduous journey. Visit the tomb of Qin Shi Huangdi, the first emperor to rule over a unified China, and discover his terracotta army as it stands guard over him for all eternity.

programme.title: Anatolia, the Caravans of Asia Minor
programme.desc: At the heart of the Anatolian plateau, visit the first of the Caravanserai that once dotted trading stations long the ancient Silk Road. The Caravanserai at Aksaray is the perfect example of architecture representing the Seljuq dynasty, the first empire in the region beginning in the 10th century.

programme.title: Iran: Assassins, Emperors and Magi
programme.desc: Begin in Iran’s Silk Road office where it is made clear that Iran has a goal of linking all countries along the illustrious road together. Then, high above sea level, explore the ruins of Hassan-i Sabbah fortress, the hideout of a movement known as “Hashshashins,” essentially drug smoking assassins.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

programme.title: Polynesia
programme.desc: Experience Polynesia’s rich sea life, crystal blue waters, and vibrant cultures. Tour the diverse reefs of the coral, sea turtle rehabilitation centers, and the many islands and atolls. Participate in the oyster-cultivation process at the major pearl farm, and tour dramatic Marquesas Islands.

programme.title: Montreal
programme.desc: Two of the most unique cities in the world are just north of New England. Here you will find brie, pate, jewel box-patisseries, and “s’il vous plait” right along with bagels, maple syrup, hockey, delis, and bocce ball. Those who forged Montreal and Quebec City braved much to see them flourish.

programme.title: Nova Scotia & Newfoundland
programme.desc: From the charming fishing towns of Nova Scotia to the vast wilderness of Newfoundland, explore the last great open spaces of Eastern North America. A touch of New England, a dash of Germany, here a British fort, there an Irish brogue, the area was peopled by the descendants of hardy colonists.

programme.title: Food, Drink, & Culture
programme.desc: In Istanbul’s Spice Market, brown-gold paprika is carefully molded into pyramids. Cinnamon, cumin, ginger, and cardamom infuse the air. From haggis in Scotland to soba and tea in Japan, from asada in Argentina to bibimbap in Korea, food and drink help illustrate the culture and people of a location.

programme.title: Asian Cities
programme.desc: From the world’s largest city, Tokyo, to the colorful chaos of Delhi, and from the modern miracle of Seoul to the teeming streets of Bangkok, this is your passport to the high-tech marvels and back-street secrets of four of the world’s most amazing cities Asian Cities.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: Yellowstone: America's First National Park
programme.desc: Vast, beautiful, and untamed, Yellowstone's wilderness ignites the imagination like no other national park. Get a ringside seat for the geothermal wonders, geyser gazing, and diversity of wildlife that gave Yellowstone the nickname, "America's Serengeti."

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba is a Caribbean Hotspot. The island is a combination of gorgeous landscapes and a unique way of life. Travel from the Guanahacabibes Peninsula to Guantanamo. In Havana, meet students that wonder about their future prospects: exile or revolution?

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: A Mystical World
programme.desc: Known as Brazil's capital of happiness, Salvador da Bahia offers fruitful local markets, and rich Bahian cuisine. Here, Tony takes part in a traditional local ceremony, and experiences the culinary talents of the famous Bahian artist of the kitchen - Chef Dada.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: Louisville
programme.desc: And we are off! We learn the history of the world famous Kentucky Derby, and call our shot, at one of America's most famous brands, Louisville Slugger. Also, we zip line in the world's only underground zip line attraction, and learn about Muhammad Ali's legacy at the Ali Center.

programme.title: Oslo
programme.desc: Set sail to Oslo, Norway. Climb the fort walls at Akershus Fortress and discover the North and South Poles at the Fram Museum. Then, unearth ancient Viking ship treasures at the Viking Ship Museum, and we will brave the open waters of the Pacific with Thor Heyerdahl at the Kon-tiki museum.

programme.title: Chile - Desert Voices
programme.desc: Known as the driest desert on Earth, the Atacama stretches 1,500 miles along the Andes Cordillera and attracts visitors from all over the world. The intense drought this region experiences helps preserve archaeological sites and geologic features dating back to the origins of the Likan Antai people.

programme.title: Sri Lanka - The Emerald Isle
programme.desc: Sri Lanka is principally known for its heavenly beaches, bold-green mountains and forests, its glorious waterfalls, and renowned tea plantations. It has begun to preserve its ecological resources, and respect the environment more and more, so that everyone may enjoy the land's bounty over time.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: Necessary Parties
programme.desc: 14-year-old Chris Mills throws a wrench in his parents’ plans to divorce by hiring Archie Corelli, an auto-mechanic by day and a lawyer by night, to sue his parents and ultimately disrupt their plans to end their marriage.

programme.title: Safe Harbor
programme.desc: Doug and Robbie are about to set sail on a long trip when they unexpectedly find themselves foster parenting a group of troubled teenage boys. The experience changes their lives for the better, and they decide to stay in town and run the foster home for boys permanently.

programme.title: Take Me Home: The John Denver Story
programme.desc: John Denver achieved fame, fortune, and acclaim for his iconic country-pop music, but his sunny personality masked private pain and dark secrets that his celebrity could never heal.

programme.title: Part 5
programme.desc: As Charlie energetically continues his acting career, he and Syd must figure out a way to bring stability to their family. Syd’s new job gets them started on the right foot, but to stay afloat, Syd and Charlie will need to work together.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis travels to the Gulf Coast for Cruisin' the Coast.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis checks out the Wellborn Muscle Car Collection.

programme.title: Shaytana's Eye
programme.desc: The peaceful Kingdom of Kale is thrown into chaos after the Citadel is overthrown by the dark forces of Kreel and Xax. After his family farm is destroyed by the Xaxian army, young William Tell is visited by the mystical Kalem who reveals that he has been chosen to seek the legendary Crystal Arrow.

programme.title: Swarm
programme.desc: Princess Vara has fallen ill, and the group is taken in by Harana, a healer and leader of a group called The Watchers. She leads them to a bountiful valley which does not seem to appear on any map. But it soon becomes evident that this idyllic valley is secretly controlled by Kreel.

programme.title: Combat
programme.desc: William is in despair, believing that the spirit of Kalem has been overtaken by the dark forces. Conflict arises amidst the group, and Aruna goes after Xax, but gets herself captured. William joins a band of prisoners in order to sneak into the Citadel to save Aruna.

programme.title: Starcrossed Lovers
programme.desc: Parsons' good-hearted sidekick Ben is now a member of the Robinson family group, but David objects when he discovers that Ben is in love with his daughter Joanna. Meanwhile, Emily must act as midwife when Elizabeth prepares to give birth.

programme.title: Thanksgiving Angel; Blind Skydiver Sees; Thanksgiving Feeding Needy; African Hijack
programme.desc: A poor mother of two can only afford to give her kids a meager Thanksgiving meal, when an elderly neighbor they had never met invites them to eat Thanksgiving dinner with her. When the mother returns the next day the to thank the woman, the apartment had been empty for years.

programme.title: God's Voice; McKay's Pennies; Doctor Rises from Ghetto; Ryan's Angels
programme.desc: A young Ben Carson turns his life around and becomes the youngest Chief of Pediatric Neurosurgery in the United States. A voice in the middle of the night told a bedridden hospital patient to "get up". She got up and was cured of her nerve disorder. And more miraculous stories.

programme.title: The Boy Who Loved Trolls
programme.desc: When 12-year-old Paul's wish that the wonderful stories he reads would come true is realized, he discovers a troll and a mermaid under a bridge. It turns out that the troll has less than a day to live, and Paul must choose to risk everything to save him.

programme.title: Episode 1
programme.desc: Giles Gordon, his Mom, and his Grandpa move to the scenic coastal town of Sunset Cove. As Giles settles into his new routine and school life at Atlantis High School, he quickly discovers that Sunset Cove is not the paradise he envisaged, and nothing is ever quite what it seems.

programme.title: Episode 2
programme.desc: As Giles pursues the attention of enigmatic Octavia Vermont, he upsets the school jock, Josh Montana, who idolizes the exceptionally vain Coach Shane. But that is the least of Giles’ problems. Principal Violet Profusion is revealed to be involved with Lew Siffer, a frightening local entrepreneur.

programme.title: The Prodigal
programme.desc: The year is 1850 in America’s Wild West, and Jess crosses paths with a trouble-making thief named Aran. Although he has been betrayed, Jess feels empathy towards Aran, and decides to accompany him to his family farm, where unfortunately, more surprises and conflict await them.

programme.title: Brothers Keeper
programme.desc: For most of her adult life, Toni James has been responsible for her kid brother, Freddy, who was born mentally challenged. On a business trip to The Dream Motel, Jesse shows Toni what her life would be like without Freddy.

programme.title: The End is Just the_Beginning - Part 1
programme.desc: Out on a lonely road, Jesse meets an old friend and soon finds himself at The Dream Motel. All seems good there, until he meets Mr. Darke.

programme.title: Lucy with George Burns
programme.desc: Upon visiting the bank Lucy works for, George Burns discovers Lucy’s instinctive style of comedic humor and asks her to become a partner in his show. Mr. Mooney, who believes this is the perfect opportunity to rid himself of Lucy at the bank, accepts the offer to become her talent agent.

programme.title: Lucy Gets a Roommate
programme.desc: To cut down on expenses, Lucy advertises for a roommate, selecting a shy Librarian named Carol Bradford. To get Carol to come out of her shell, Lucy and Mary Jane throw a party and invite a group of musicians to perform.

programme.title: The Night the Roof Fell In
programme.desc: Both Rob and Laura each experienced an unpleasant day, and it only gets worse when they meet at home for further argument. Only their pet goldfish, and their apartments four walls, can report the truth as Laura and Rob spin colorful, self-aggrandizing versions to their friends about their argument.

programme.title: The Fish Story
programme.desc: To prove a point, Ozzie begins to circulate a rumor in the neighborhood by tricking his best friend, Thorny, into believing that the fish are biting like crazy in Mud Basin.

programme.title: Part 1
programme.desc: Amid a family life on the verge of ruin, yet one alive with the spirit of performance, a mischievous, resourceful Charlie, and his brother Sydney, grapple with keeping the few threads that hold the quilt of their family’s spirit together.

programme.title: Never Name a Duck
programme.desc: Ritchie becomes very attached to two baby ducks that were left over from a show and decides to adopt them. Rob faces the daunting task of making Ritchie understand the consequence of attempting to keep wild animals as pets that may be happier living in the wild.

programme.title: Paws to the Rescue
programme.desc: Upon deciding to testify against his former employer at a tobacco company, Harry Burton’s son, Charlie, is threatened by two thugs hired by the company to thwart Harry’s testimony. That is when the family’s two dogs come to the rescue.

programme.title: Part 5
programme.desc: Sara learns the hard way that generosity is not always repaid with kindness, but that does not stop Sara from conducting herself in the manner she is accustomed to. For, deep down she knows that the strongest light of faith resides within.

programme.title: The Spirit of Kale
programme.desc: During an attempt to infiltrate Kreel in his stronghold, Kalem transforms into a bird but is sensed by Shaytana's Eye and badly wounded. To heal herself she must drink from the Crystal Stream, but she is far too weak to make the journey alone. So, Will and Aruna must assist her.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis heads to Macungie, PA for Wheels of Time

programme.title: Skeleton in the Cupboard
programme.desc: The Painter family have been magicians for generations, and 14-year-old Cherry wants to be the first world-class female magician. Her Grandad created a world-famous trick called 'The Skeleton in the Cupboard,’ but is it worth revisiting?

programme.title: Between Life and Death
programme.desc: 12-year-old Jamie Irving and his father, Rick, are opposites. When Rick discovers illegal activities at his company, he becomes entangled in a mystery that results in his spirit disconnecting from his body, and only Jamie can see him.

programme.title: Book 1: The Island of Adventure (Part 1)
programme.desc: When they discover their guardian is sick, Jack and Lucy-Ann accept Philip's offer to spend the rest of the holiday at his new cliff top home in Cornwall. There they meet Joe, a friendly man who helps Philip's widowed mother Allison, at her Art Gallery, and Philip's sister, Dinah.

programme.title: Book 1: The Island of Adventure (Part 2)
programme.desc: After finding an old smugglers' tunnel while exploring, the boys fall into it and are unable to climb out. In the tunnel, they discover stairs which lead to Craggy Tops' cellar. After Allison is befriended by the mysterious stranger, Bill, he offers to take the children out for a boat trip.

programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis travels to Redding, CA for Kool April Nites.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.
