programme.title: Flathorn Lake 1
programme.desc: Sometimes you don’t have to go far to have a great trip in Alaska. The lake Larry Csonka is fishing this week is almost in the backyard of his house in Wasilla. And he’s taking enough new Hobie kayaks for the whole crew!

programme.title: Flathorn Lake 2
programme.desc: A common complaint about pike is that they are really bony fish. That’s not entirely true; they don’t really have more bones... but their bones are shaped like ‘Y’s. So when you have a batch of pike this big, you better know what you’re doing when you go to filet them. This week on NAPA’s North to Alaska, you’ll see how it’s done.

programme.title: Squirrel Masters
programme.desc: The greatest squirrel hunting competition of all time!

programme.title: Springfield Armory RO Elite Operator 10mm
programme.desc: The Springfield Armory 1911 RO Elite series ups the ante in power by introducing it's newest model in 10mm. Kyle Lamb shows us how to shoot fast without double-tapping in Stay in the Fight. In Pros Vs Joes Jim Tarr using a revolver against a pistol.

programme.title: Larry Potterfield's Nearly Perfect Safari Rifle
programme.desc: Host Joe Mantegna visits Larry Potterfield who has created, what he calls, the perfect safari rifle. Well...almost perfect.

programme.title: Mark Menendez - Kentucky
programme.desc: Like Zonais Awesome Fishing Show, fishing is unpredictable. Mark Zona fishes with the best anglers on the planet to catch anything wearing fins.

programme.title: Destination Options in Overdrive
programme.desc: The In-Fisherman staff keeps you flying under the radar, as they travel to Mississippi for monster crappies, highlight peak fishing options for one of North America’s greatest fisheries on the waters of Green Bay, and head to coastal British Columbia for spectacular king salmon.

programme.title: Stingray 216, Sea Fox 228 Commander, Stamas 33T
programme.desc: Today, on Florida Sportsman Best Boat... for the family in search of comfort features and fishing capabilities in an affordable package, we’ll be taking a look at the Stingray 216CC Deck Boat ; if you require a boat designed to exceed the needs of the mos demanding Captain, as well as accommodate the entire family, we’ll be looking at the SeaFox 228 Commander ; and...for those looking to blend offshore adventure with luxury and comfort, we’ll be taking a look at the innovative Stamas 33T.

programme.title: “Mini-Grander” Dreams, Classic L&H 33
programme.desc: L&H Boats works to complete the 33 on time for delivery day; the experts at Two Rivers Boatworks continue rigging on the 36 Yellowfin; George LaBonte joins dreamboat owner Rick Cerrito aboard his fully-restored 1978 Formula 233; and...Stuart Boatworks starts the build of a very custom 27.

programme.title: Magic City Bones, Permit, Blackfin & Sailfish with Capt. Peter Miller and Capt. Joe Gonzalez
programme.desc: Miami offers some of the best inshore and offshore fishing on the planet, despite suffering from water issues and loss of habitat. Witness World Class fishing for Bonefish, Permit, Blackfin Tuna and Sailfish while these legendary Captains discuss the importance of estuary protection.

programme.title: Alaska-Yukon Moose Archery Hunt
programme.desc: The Alaska-Yukon Moose hunt can be challenging, exhilarating and rewarding. This hunt is no exception. Greg is pushing his luck with a late-season foray into the snow-covered hills of the Yukon in search of adventure, a big bull and a great trophy. He sees a few great moose before coming across a bull he can't turn down. If you love moose, you'll love this hunt.

programme.title: Shankfest 5 Part 2
programme.desc: Shankfest 5 Group 2 arrives in camp to Choctaw Hunting Lodge with more hogs and rams on the menu.

programme.title: Best of Season 9
programme.desc: All the best hunts of Season 9 cut down to 30 minutes of nothing but arrows flingin and bullets flyin!

programme.title: Wild Wild West
programme.desc: Bone Collector and Realtree's Spring Thunder hit Wyoming, South Dakota, and Montana all in one nonstop turkey killin show!

programme.title: Our Dwellings Shape Us
programme.desc: A gorgeous quail hunt at the famed Brays Island, where Chris Dorsey is joined by General Walter Boomer and Gerald McRaney.

programme.title: A Mayan Fowl Play
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey and good friend Francisco Bergaz travel into the thick jungles of the Yucatan Peninsula to hunt the gorgeous ocellated turkey.

programme.title: Yellow Creek Wyoming
programme.desc: Wind and cold weather are on the docket for hunters in Wyoming with Dallas Safari Club’s Outfitter of the Year B. Joe Coy. Getting into range of these mature whitetails is tough when the stiff wind keeps changing directions on Mr. Whitetail.

programme.title: No Laughing Matter
programme.desc: Larry Weishuhn – the Elvis of deer hunters – heads to Machen Ranch in south Texas to rattle in a mature whitetail buck during the peak of the rut. Senator John McCain joins Larry to discuss the second amendment and the future of deer hunting.

programme.title: Top of the Flyway
programme.desc: It's an annual pilgrimage at the as Chris Dorsey and brother Joe venture to Alberta to catch the beginning of North America's annual waterfowl migration.

programme.title: Birds by the Clouds
programme.desc: Enjoy a World class cast and blast as Argentina's unmatched wingshooting f doves, ducks and perdiz challenge Chris and Joe Dorsey's shoulders. Then they take to the water to cast and acrobatic golden dorado.

programme.title: Stuck In The Rut
programme.desc: Jeff hunts the peak of the rut & gives some shed hunting tips for starting your young retriever!

programme.title: Hot and Hevi
programme.desc: It’s the Wisconsin Waterfowl Opener & Pickett dominates an upland hunt in the afternoon.

programme.title: Offshore Gulf Grouper
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Seth Hayes for some incredible offshore gag grouper action off the coast of Ft.Myers.

programme.title: Backwater Series in the Everglades
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Donnie Kish in search of redfish and the first place trophy.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 2
programme.desc: It’s Day 2 of the Golden Fly Tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob is fishing tournament champion Andy Mill and Bou is fishing his friend Paul Nute.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 3
programme.desc: It’s Day 3 of the Golden Fly tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob and Andy Mill have had a productive week, but will need a strong finish to win the event.

programme.title: Young Salt, Old Spirit
programme.desc: Armed with the skills of generations past, rough and tumble New Englanders teach the SFTV crew how to catch the region's sporty summertime species.

programme.title: Atlantic Gladiators
programme.desc: New England pelagics like swordfish and bluefin tuna bring more than sport. It's a heavyweight, high octane battle, and the angler is the underdog.

programme.title: Catch Me If You Can
programme.desc: Three days, five release flags, 400 photos: the SFTV crew and Marlin magazine join forces to chase blue marlin and sailfish at Panama's Tropic Star Lodge.

programme.title: Jacks Be Roiling
programme.desc: When word gets out that Jack Crevalle are in a feeding frenzy, Justin and fellow Captain Kyle Pitts speed down the Intracoastal Waterway to find them doing just that.

programme.title: Aftermath Bite
programme.desc: Travis and Justin head out after Hurricane Michael and find it hard to keep fish off the hook

programme.title: Postpawn Smallies
programme.desc: Fishing for postspawn smallmouth bass. Subtle lures and swimming retrieves match the depth and mood of smallies on the move

programme.title: Eagle Lake Musky
programme.desc: Tackling giant muskies on Eagle Lake in northwest Ontario. How to cover water and convert follows into fish on the line

programme.title: Artificial Crappie
programme.desc: Fishing the deep weededges for summer crappies. Jigs and micro crankbaits target different depth ranges.

programme.title: Florida Tarpon
programme.desc: This is Ford's Fishing Frontiers, and for host Flip Pallot, it is a homecoming to the Florida Everglades, where he was raised. Joining him on this south Florida expedition is Rob Fordyce, veteran fishing guide and a young friend that Flip was once privileged to mentor.

programme.title: Ford Frontier Fishing
programme.desc: Host, Flip Pallot, heads back to his roots, down in the Florida Everglades, on this episode of Ford's Fishing Frontiers. Rob Fordyce and his former mentor, Flip, share a flats boat, as they cast toward the mangroves in pursuit of some of their favorite game fish: snook, grouper and the silver king - tarpon.

programme.title: Cedar Lake Skis
programme.desc: Cedar Lake in Perrault Falls, Ontario, Canada, is a diverse musky fishery with multiple water colors and structural elements. Jim Saric and musky hunter Bob Turgeon grind through post-frontal conditions and sift through shallow cover utilizing boatside tactics to trigger Cedar Lake Skis to bite.

programme.title: Lake Louise II
programme.desc: A Year-Round Destination by Road

programme.title: Show Me The Bulls
programme.desc: CJ Buck, President and CEO of Buck Knives, and former Indy car driver Johnny Unser, Jr. take on Idaho in archery season, while Cameron Hanes looks to connect in Colorado.

programme.title: Expect The Unexpected
programme.desc: PBR Bullrider Dustin Elliott hunts elk in Colorado, while Team Elk host Brandon Bates manages an unexpected situation in Wyoming.

programme.title: Isenhour Ranch Texas
programme.desc: It is December in South Texas, and whitetail expert Larry Weishuhn is guiding Pam Zates on a whitetail hunt. They each have a tag, so Larry could transition from guide to hunter if the right buck shows up. He also discusses the need for ample doe harvests to keep the whitetail population healthy.

programme.title: Timberghost Ranch Iowa
programme.desc: Despite 50 years of hunting experience, Larry Weishuhn can still be the victim of the dreaded buck fever. Larry is hunting at Timberghost Ranch in Iowa, where the buck of a lifetime waits... if he can hit it.

programme.title: The Harvest You Reap
programme.desc: Ron and Betsy Spomer have purchased their forever-home - a spectacular ranch in Idaho - and this is Ron's first season hunting his new honey hole.

programme.title: Get Their Good Tidings
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey returns to the mountains of Colorado to hunt mule deer in the rut.

programme.title: Hooray 1
programme.desc: Michael Waddell and T- Bone Turner are back at the Hooray Ranch in Kansas to start off Season 11 of Bone Collector!

programme.title: Hot and Hevi
programme.desc: It’s the Wisconsin Waterfowl Opener & Pickett dominates an upland hunt in the afternoon.

programme.title: Flint Oak Upland
programme.desc: Join Jeff Fuller, along with his sons, Clayton and Callahan, and the dogs of Soggy Acres Retrievers as they travel to Flint Oak Hunting Resort in Kansas for an upland hunt to remember.

programme.title: Roborace - Our first music EP is out!
programme.desc: Initially, project Roborace is the extreme competition of full-size electric racing cars driven by artificial intelligence. The cars were designed by Daniel Simon, who previously worked on vehicles for movies such as "Tron: Legacy", "Oblivion", sequels of "Star Wars" and others. Introducing the coming "Season Beta" of the robot competition, this futuristic project evolves with starting its own original music band in collaboration with several contemporary musicians from various countries to create their first EP "Beta". The work was made together with Russian synth-music artist Vlad Green (aka TæT Music) and Belgian progressive drummer Benjamin Baert. More releases to come soon.

programme.title: Animation: Dynamic All-Wheel Steering – Maneuvering And Parking
programme.desc: An advance in all-wheel steering, the Dynamic All-wheel Steering that is optional in the Audi A6, A7, and A8, is standard equipment in the S8. It is currently the top technology among Audi’s steering systems and combines dynamic steering on the front axle with rear-axle steering. With that system, Audi is exploring the limits of what is physically possible. The system offers significant benefits, specifically in the threshold range. It combines direct, sporty steering response with masterful driving stability or, in brief: manageability with extremely high precision.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 e-tron – Interior and package
programme.desc: With the Q4 e-tron, Audi is presenting a true all-rounder – it is a confident companion for everyday life and leisure, and is suitable in every way as a household’s main car. At 4,590 millimeters (15.1 ft) long, 1,865 millimeters (6.1 ft) wide, and 1,613 millimeters (5.3 ft) high, the exterior dimensions of the Q4 e-tron place it in the larger compact SUV segment. The architecture of the modular electric drive system (MEB) on which the compact electric SUV from Audi is based enables a completely new division of space. While the front overhang measures just 86 centimeters (33.9 in), the wheelbase measures a generous 2.76 meters (9.1 ft) – even more than in the medium-sized SUV segment. The resulting interior measures 1.83 meters (6.0 ft) in length, which is similar to a large full-size class SUV.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Interior Design and Seating Position
programme.desc: The fully electric gran turismo gives new impetus to the Audi design language: It is a dynamic sculpture that stands on the road as if sculpted from a full volume. The Audi e-tron GT proves: The packaging of an electric car with its large battery and the fascinating design of a gran turismo with a flat silhouette and powerful proportions are no contradiction. This is made possible by a recess in the battery pack. The passengers in the rear can put their feet in what is known as the foot garage, which allows them to sit in a lower position and enjoy generous headroom despite the flat roof line. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Electric Quattro and Recuperation
programme.desc: The e-tron GT quattro and the RS e-tron GT usually drive with electric all-wheel drive, only the “efficiency” mode of the Audi drive select dynamic handling system prioritizing the front-wheel drive. In event of a slippery road surface, high power requirements, or fast cornering, the electric motor for rear-wheel drive is also activated here, and around five times faster than with a mechanical quattro drivetrain. The electric all-wheel drive regulates the drive torque distribution between the axles – continuously, fully variably, and within a few thousandths of a second. The quattro principle of the four-wheel drive that Audi introduced to the market more than 40 years ago presents itself on a new, fascinating technological level. When the driver releases the right-hand pedal, the drive usually switches to sailing, allowing the gran turismo to glide with elegance and efficiency. By contrast, the car recuperates in overrun mode in the “dynamic” mode of Audi drive select. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 Sportback e-tron – Electric quattro: Torque Distribution and Cooling
programme.desc: The electric all-wheel drive in the Q4 e-tron top models has an asynchronous motor (ASM) on the front wheels that can rev at up to 14,000 rpm. It is installed coaxially and has combined cooling with coolant and oil. The principal advantages of the ASM are its short-term overload capacity and the minimal drag losses when it is inactive – these are important because the front motor does not contribute to the drive in the majority of driving situations for reasons of efficiency. - Audi Q4 Sportback e-tron: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.9–16.6 (WLTP); 17.9 – 15.6 (NEDC) Combined CO2 emissions in g/km: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes.

programme.title: Animation: Dynamic All-Wheel Steering – Maneuvering And Parking
programme.desc: An advance in all-wheel steering, the Dynamic All-wheel Steering that is optional in the Audi A6, A7, and A8, is standard equipment in the S8. It is currently the top technology among Audi’s steering systems and combines dynamic steering on the front axle with rear-axle steering. With that system, Audi is exploring the limits of what is physically possible. The system offers significant benefits, specifically in the threshold range. It combines direct, sporty steering response with masterful driving stability or, in brief: manageability with extremely high precision.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 e-tron – Interior and package
programme.desc: With the Q4 e-tron, Audi is presenting a true all-rounder – it is a confident companion for everyday life and leisure, and is suitable in every way as a household’s main car. At 4,590 millimeters (15.1 ft) long, 1,865 millimeters (6.1 ft) wide, and 1,613 millimeters (5.3 ft) high, the exterior dimensions of the Q4 e-tron place it in the larger compact SUV segment. The architecture of the modular electric drive system (MEB) on which the compact electric SUV from Audi is based enables a completely new division of space. While the front overhang measures just 86 centimeters (33.9 in), the wheelbase measures a generous 2.76 meters (9.1 ft) – even more than in the medium-sized SUV segment. The resulting interior measures 1.83 meters (6.0 ft) in length, which is similar to a large full-size class SUV.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Interior Design and Seating Position
programme.desc: The fully electric gran turismo gives new impetus to the Audi design language: It is a dynamic sculpture that stands on the road as if sculpted from a full volume. The Audi e-tron GT proves: The packaging of an electric car with its large battery and the fascinating design of a gran turismo with a flat silhouette and powerful proportions are no contradiction. This is made possible by a recess in the battery pack. The passengers in the rear can put their feet in what is known as the foot garage, which allows them to sit in a lower position and enjoy generous headroom despite the flat roof line. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Electric Quattro and Recuperation
programme.desc: The e-tron GT quattro and the RS e-tron GT usually drive with electric all-wheel drive, only the “efficiency” mode of the Audi drive select dynamic handling system prioritizing the front-wheel drive. In event of a slippery road surface, high power requirements, or fast cornering, the electric motor for rear-wheel drive is also activated here, and around five times faster than with a mechanical quattro drivetrain. The electric all-wheel drive regulates the drive torque distribution between the axles – continuously, fully variably, and within a few thousandths of a second. The quattro principle of the four-wheel drive that Audi introduced to the market more than 40 years ago presents itself on a new, fascinating technological level. When the driver releases the right-hand pedal, the drive usually switches to sailing, allowing the gran turismo to glide with elegance and efficiency. By contrast, the car recuperates in overrun mode in the “dynamic” mode of Audi drive select. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 Sportback e-tron – Electric quattro: Torque Distribution and Cooling
programme.desc: The electric all-wheel drive in the Q4 e-tron top models has an asynchronous motor (ASM) on the front wheels that can rev at up to 14,000 rpm. It is installed coaxially and has combined cooling with coolant and oil. The principal advantages of the ASM are its short-term overload capacity and the minimal drag losses when it is inactive – these are important because the front motor does not contribute to the drive in the majority of driving situations for reasons of efficiency. - Audi Q4 Sportback e-tron: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.9–16.6 (WLTP); 17.9 – 15.6 (NEDC) Combined CO2 emissions in g/km: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Electric Quattro and Recuperation
programme.desc: The e-tron GT quattro and the RS e-tron GT usually drive with electric all-wheel drive, only the “efficiency” mode of the Audi drive select dynamic handling system prioritizing the front-wheel drive. In event of a slippery road surface, high power requirements, or fast cornering, the electric motor for rear-wheel drive is also activated here, and around five times faster than with a mechanical quattro drivetrain. The electric all-wheel drive regulates the drive torque distribution between the axles – continuously, fully variably, and within a few thousandths of a second. The quattro principle of the four-wheel drive that Audi introduced to the market more than 40 years ago presents itself on a new, fascinating technological level. When the driver releases the right-hand pedal, the drive usually switches to sailing, allowing the gran turismo to glide with elegance and efficiency. By contrast, the car recuperates in overrun mode in the “dynamic” mode of Audi drive select. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.desc: Ron Balicki is a full instructor of Maphilindo Silat under Guru Dan Inosanto. Inosanto is one of the most sought after martial artists and Ron has been his student for over twenty years. Instruction includes how to close on an opponent from various defensive entries such as outside, split, inside and reverse split. Takedowns include such techniques as single and double hand, neck throw, leg sweeps and trips, arm drag down and much more. Program highlights techniques from Silat system such as Kari, Hari Mau, Mande Muda, Pentjak Silat and Kali Kuntao Silat.

programme.title: Laura McKenzie's Traveler
programme.desc: Malta- - Laura visits a re-enactment of La Guardia, which represents a military performance that used to take place in the time of the Knights of St. John. Plus, the walled city of Mdina then Valletta Gozo, The Blue Grotto, St. Paul’s Catacombs, and the Temple of Hagar Qim. Finally, Laura rounds out her trip with an excursion to Ggantia, the oldest free-standing structure in the world.

programme.title: The Bay- The Beginning
programme.desc: Episode 4- - Much to Sara’s surprise, event planner Sofia Madison, the wife of Mayor Jack Madison, arrives at the Garrett estate for Brian and Zoey’s wedding. Zoey’s father Harold also shows up in town for the wedding and sets a surprised and uninformed Zoey off. An adulterous Marly and her lover Manny Ramos are interrupted when Manny’s sister Janice unexpectedly turns up needing his help and revealing some shocking news. Lee confronts Commissioner Lex Martin about Sara and Lex’s affair. Later, Pete returns to Bay City and confronts Sara. Lee discovers his stepson Brian is keeping secrets as Zoey has a change of heart.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: S1 E22 | Cardi B and Raven Symoné team up to pull off a lesbian wedding on Facebook's Cardi Tries, before we celebrate Indigenous Peoples’ day by spotlighting two-spirit voices, Canada's Drag Race's Ilona Verley and Being Thunder's Sherenté Harris. Later we look at what a sh*t show Dave Chappelle's Netflix special, The Closer, and North Carolina Lieutenant Governor Mark Robinson's anti-trans rant have created. Finally, we feel inspired by Tom Daley speaking out against homophobia at the 2021 Attitude awards, and Drag Race UK's Charity Kase opening up about what life looks like as an HIV-positive person.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Hot Trash
programme.desc: S1 E1 | D'Arcy dishes the dirt about the Capitol Insurrection, Pence's fly, and much, much, more! D'Arcy dishes the dirt about Armie Hammer, Sex and the City, #BussitChallenge, and more!

programme.title: Submission Possible
programme.desc: S1 E3 | In Episode Three, Young explores the quirky and kinky city of Portland, Oregon, a city full of people who stand up for what they believe in. Portland isn’t afraid to remind us all that kink is political AF! From Strippers fighting for equal rights and pay amidst a pandemic to Foodie Activism for Sex Workers, Young connects with fellow sexual revolutionaries making a difference in their city. Madison’s explorations lead them to an amazing cast of characters including Nikeisah C. Newton, a chef turned sex worker activist, Cat Hollis - a stripper rights activist and organizer for the Portland Stripper’s Strike, Arabelle Raphael - sex worker and fetishist, and the donut daddy of our dreams, Dadi Iris, who shows us just what those donut holes are really for!

programme.title: The Queen Of Ireland
programme.desc: How one man in a dress is changing the world. The Queen of Ireland is a documentary that follows drag queen Panti Bliss: part glamorous aunt, part Jessica Rabbit, she's a wittily incisive performer with charisma to burn who is widely regarded as one of the best drag queens in the world. Created by Rory O’Neill, Panti is also an accidental activist and in her own words ‘a court jester, whose role is to say the un-sayable’. In recent years, Rory has become a figurehead for LGBT rights in Ireland and since the 2014 scandal around Pantigate, his fight for equality and against homophobia has become recognised across the world. The Queen of Ireland follows drag queen Panti Bliss. Created by Rory O’Neill, In recent years, Rory and Panti have become a figurehead for LGBT rights in Ireland and since the 2014 scandal around Pantigate, his fight for equality and against homophobia has become recognised across the world.

programme.title: Victor's Last Class
programme.desc: A brazen acting teacher suffering from chronic pain announces he is going to end his life, and spends the next five months hashing the decision out with the young filmmaker who attempts to change his mind.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Equality U
programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

programme.title: Jobriath A.D.
programme.desc: Known as the first openly gay rock star, Jobriath’s reign was a brief two years. Done in by over-hyped publicity, shunned by the gay community, and dismissed by critics, Jobriath retreated to the Chelsea Hotel, where he died forgotten, one of the earliest casualties of AIDS. But years later, new fans discover his music, and acts such as The Pet Shop Boys, Def Leppard, and Morrissey cite him as an influence. Experience the heartbreaking, unbelievable story of the one, the only, Jobriath.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.desc: A look into what labels a life in current LGBT America. Fifty conversations exploring the many different shades of being “gay” in America. This conversation focuses on the degrees and varying perceptions about how people define themselves, their lives, struggles and triumphs.

programme.title: The Abominable Crime
programme.desc: The Abominable Crime is a riveting documentary that explores the religious-based culture of homophobia in Jamaica through the eyes of gay Jamaicans forced to choose between their homeland and their lives. With personal accounts from Jamaica's leading human-rights activists and a young lesbian single mother who survives a brutal anti-gay shooting, the film's characters take the audience on an emotionally gripping journey over four years and across five countries, offering an intimate first-person perspective on the risks and challenges of seeking asylum abroad.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle
programme.desc: L'illustre Orchestra Filarmonica di Berlino, la Berliner Philharmoniker, ha fatto dell'Europakonzert una tradizione. Ogni anno i suoi musicisti celebrano la fondazione della loro orchestra in una città europea diversa. Nel 2008 si sono esibiti sotto alla direzione del grande direttore d'orchestra Sir Simon Rattle al Conservatorio Tchaikovsky di Mosca. In programma: Il Concerto per violino n. 1 in SOL minore di Max Bruch, la Sinfonia n. 7 di Beethoven e la Sinfonia di Igor Stravinsky in tre movimenti.

programme.title: Giuseppe Verdi: Nabucco
programme.desc: Nel 586 a.C., Nabucco, re di Babilonia, tenne gli ebrei prigionieri in Babilonia. Questa è l'origine del famoso coro Va, pensiero, o Coro degli schiavi, un poema lirico che è considerato un inno alla libertà. L'orchestra e il coro dell'Opera di Zurigo sotto la direzione di Fabio Luisi eseguono con brio questa famosa opera di Giuseppe Verdi.

programme.title: Renaud Capuçon carte blanche
programme.desc: Il Festival "Les Coups de Cœur à Chantilly" concede a Renaud Capuçon ucarta bianca come solista e direttore musicale dei Solisti dell'Accademia Menuhin. Questa accademia, fondata in Svizzera dal famoso violinista Yehudi Menuhin (1916-1999), accoglie dal 1977 i migliori strumentisti ad arco e li riunisce per concerti in tutto il mondo.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Boris Berezovsky
programme.desc: Boris Berezovsky è considerato uno dei migliori rappresentanti della scuola pianistica russa, soprattutto per la sua potente tecnica. Per il 15° anniversario del Verbier Festival, in programma un recital con la Sonata in si minore di Franz Liszt, seguito da brani di Schumann. Un vero e proprio viaggio nel romanticismo.

programme.title: Qwest TV Classical
programme.desc: Quincy Jones mostra la ricchezza della performance classica in tutta la sua gloria e la rende accessibile a tutti. Vivi la potenza e la bellezza dei migliori concerti, opera e danza.

programme.title: Beethoven - Daniel Barenboim
programme.desc: Qui l'illustre direttore d'orchestra Daniel Barenboim suona e dirige i cinque concerti di Beethoven con l'Orchestra della Staatskapelle di Berlino in occasione del suo 65° compleanno. Il Concerto n. 5 in MI bemolle maggiore, noto come "L'Imperatore", vede il maestro rivoluzionare la forma con un primo movimento lungo seicento battute. Un'improvvisazione messa per iscritto?

programme.title: Balanchine: Jewels - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Girato al Teatro Mariinsky, questo spettacolo vede la partecipazione di alcuni dei più famosi ballerini del teatro di San Pietroburgo, tra cui Ulyana Lopatkina, Igor Zelensky e Andrian Fadeyev, accanto al direttore d'orchestra Tugan Sokhiev. I Gioielli di George Balanchine sono parte integrante del repertorio della compagnia - uno dei più grandi al mondo, sia per numero che per fama.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Evgeny Kissin
programme.desc: Autentica star del pianoforte, il musicista russo Evgeny Kissin è ospite fisso del Verbier Festival in Svizzera, dove si è esibito più volte dalla prima edizione del 1994. La Sonata per pianoforte n. 59 di Haydn, la Sonata per pianoforte n. 32 di Beethoven e la "Melodia" di Christoph Willibald Gluck da Orfeo ed Euridice offrono a Kissin l'opportunità di mostrare la portata del suo virtuosismo e il lirismo delle sue interpretazioni, ma anche il suo carisma fenomenale.

programme.title: Qwest TV Classical
programme.desc: Quincy Jones mostra la ricchezza della performance classica in tutta la sua gloria e la rende accessibile a tutti. Vivi la potenza e la bellezza dei migliori concerti, opera e danza.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle
programme.desc: L'illustre Orchestra Filarmonica di Berlino, la Berliner Philharmoniker, ha fatto dell'Europakonzert una tradizione. Ogni anno i suoi musicisti celebrano la fondazione della loro orchestra in una città europea diversa. Nel 2008 si sono esibiti sotto alla direzione del grande direttore d'orchestra Sir Simon Rattle al Conservatorio Tchaikovsky di Mosca. In programma: Il Concerto per violino n. 1 in SOL minore di Max Bruch, la Sinfonia n. 7 di Beethoven e la Sinfonia di Igor Stravinsky in tre movimenti.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: S. Prokofiev - Valery Gergiev
programme.desc: Il Festival di Pasqua di Mosca è uno degli eventi di musica classica più importanti al mondo. Vi sono presenti i più grandi solisti sotto alla direzione del più rinomato direttore d'orchestra russo, Valery Gergiev, con l'orchestra del Teatro Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo, di cui è il direttore. In un ciclo dedicato al compositore Sergei Prokofiev, il pianista russo Daniil Trifonov interpreta il Concerto per pianoforte e orchestra n. 1.

programme.title: Esa-Pekka Salonen - Joyce DiDonato
programme.desc: Dal 1994, il Festival di Verbier è un luogo d'incontro musicale internazionale nella Svizzera francese. Grandi artisti vi si esibiscono ogni anno davanti a un pubblico fedele. Nel 2015, il Festival accoglie il brillante mezzosoprano americano Joyce DiDonato. Eseguirà Summer Nights, Op. 7 di Hector Berlioz, sotto la direzione di Esa-Pekka Solonen, il famoso direttore d'orchestra finlandese. Si tratta di sei melodie francesi su bellissime poesie di Théophile Gautier da La Comédie de la mort.

programme.title: Jakub Jozef Orlinski- Il Pomo D'Oro
programme.desc: Il controtenore polacco Jakub Józef Orlinski si è guadagnato in breve tempo la reputazione di cantante dalla sorprendente padronanza vocale e dall'audacia scenica. Questo concerto riflette la tanto attesa uscita del suo primo album, Anima Sacra, un recital di arie sacre del XVIII secolo recentemente riscoperte con il gruppo barocco Il Pomo d'oro.

programme.title: PUCCINI by Julien Lestel Company
programme.desc: Le eroine del compositore Giacomo Puccini erano quasi sempre condannate a un tragico destino. Qui vengono portate sul palco accompagnate dalle arie più belle. Questa coreografia è un omaggio all'opera, e in particolare all'illustre compositore scomparso.

programme.title: B. Philharmoniker: Gershwin Night
programme.desc: Il Waldbühne di Berlino, residenza estiva dell'orchestra filarmonica della città, i Berliner Philharmoniker, è uno degli anfiteatri all'aperto più belli d'Europa. Nell'estate del 2003, il direttore d'orchestra giapponese Seji Ozawa ha diretto la famosa orchestra su successi di Gershwin come Un américain à Paris, Rhapsody in Blue, I Got Rhythm ... Ospite speciale: Il famoso trio jazz di Marcus Roberts.

programme.title: G. Puccini: Tosca - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Basata su un'opera teatrale di Victorien Sardou, l'opera Tosca ha conquistato il pubblico sin dalla sua uscita nel 1900. Questo dramma verista è sublimato dalla composizione virtuosa di Puccini. - Sotto la direzione di Sir Simon Rattle, la storia d'amore di Floria Tosca e Mario Cavaradossi si svolge e viene messa alla prova dal tirannico capo della polizia Scarpia, che governa Roma. In questa produzione, il famoso tenore argentino Marcelo Álvarez trascende la scena, accompagnato dalla sublime Kristine Opolais nel ruolo dell'eroina.

programme.title: J.S. Bach: Organ Concerts
programme.desc: Per rendere omaggio a Johann Sebastian Bach che ha servito per 27 anni come "maestro di cappella" nella chiesa di San Tommaso a Lipsia, l'organista Ullrich Böhme dà un concerto sul nuovo organo della chiesa: una replica del modello storico che suonava Bach.

programme.title: The Nutcracker - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Ed è proprio sul palco del Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo che, nel 1892, è stato creato il capolavoro di Tchaïkovski: lo Schiaccianoci. Sullo stesso palcoscenico, 120 anni dopo, l’orchestra del medesimo teatro, sotto alla bacchetta del maestro Valery Gergiev, accompagnata dal prestigioso balletto del teatro Mariinsky, ne offre una versione che non potrebbe essere più fiabesca.

programme.title: Denis Matsuev at Concertgebouw
programme.desc: Il pianista russo Denis Matsuev, uno dei più grandi virtuosi del suo strumento, si esibisce qui in un recital solista sul palcoscenico del Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. In programma ci sono le Stagioni di Tchaikovsky, un classico della musica russa per celebrare il 175° compleanno del compositore nel 2015, e un'altra opera romantica: La Kreisleriana di Schumann. Egli esegue anche l'impressionante e virtuosistico "Tre Movimenti di Petrushka" di Stravinsky.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.
